.TH "rpc_ntop" 9 "rpc_ntop" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rpc_ntop \- construct a presentation address in @buf
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "size_t" rpc_ntop
.BI "(const struct sockaddr *sap "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ","
.BI "const size_t buflen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sap" 12
socket address
.IP "buf" 12
construction area
.IP "buflen" 12
size of \fIbuf\fP, in bytes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Plants a NUL-terminated string in \fIbuf\fP and returns the length
of the string, excluding the NUL.  Otherwise zero is returned.
